
[1]subterfuge

   SUB'TERFUGE, n. [L. subter and fugio, to flee.] Literally, that to
   which a person resorts for escape or concealment; hence, a shift; an
   evasion; an artifice employed to escape censure or the force of an
   argument, or to justify opinions or conduct.

   Affect not little shifts and subterfuges, to avoid the force of an
   argument.
